'''Tolea Biqua''', sometimes known as '''TB''',<ref name="POB">{{LivingForce|The Price of Business}}</ref> was a floating city on [[Genarius]], considered the twin city of [[Varna Biqua]], and built at the direction of [[Crime lord/Legends|crime lord]] [[Riboga]] the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]]. Unlike the uniformity of other Genariusan floating cities like [[Ipsus]], Tolea Biqua was disheveled and disorganized. It was a conglomeration of clashing building styles laid out without a clear plan. Surfaces were brightly painted in primary colors, and neon tubes were frequent. From a distance, it looked beautiful, but the illusion did not hold up long when approached.<ref name="LFC">''[[Living Force Campaign Guide]]''</ref>

Tolea Biqua's radiation shields were designed to absorb and use the radiation of the [[Planet/Legends|planet's]] storms to power the city's bright lights. Without the power absorbed from the storms, in a week Tolea Biqua would use up [[Power cell/Legends|power cells]] which could power a full-sized freighter for a year.<ref name="LFC" />

Riboga would later order an office to be built there for him, although it would be used more for his personal relaxation and to spy on potential enemies, as the Hutt had other headquarters to make business.<ref name="LFC" />

Tolea Biqua centered on [[Gambling/Legends|gambling]], though almost any vice could be accommodated there, such as drinking, companionship, or addictive [[Spice/Legends|spices]], with no public discussions or negotiations. There were many gambling establishments to be found there. One of the most profitable since [[53 BBY/Legends|53 BBY]] was [[Riboga's Barge]].<ref name="LFC" /> One of the many things to gamble upon were the races through the tunnels of [[Eskaron]].<ref name="POB" /> Due to the city's reputation as a den of iniquity, it had touristic appeal among certain kinds of sentients: Newly wealthy [[Gungan/Legends|Gungan]] [[Brute (Gungan)|Brute]] aimed to go to Tolea Biqua on vacation to spend a part of his money.<ref name="cp">{{LivingForce|Clouds of Genarius: Clouded Paths}}</ref>

Tolea Biqua had no law-enforcement agency. Individuals protected their own interests with their personal weaponry. Even [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] were attacked, and the [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Masters]] strongly suggested that [[Padawan/Legends|Padawans]] were always in groups.<ref name="POB" /> Nevertheless, Tolea Biqua had its own jail.<ref name="MW">{{LivingForce|Between the Worlds: MidWorld}}</ref>

Bodyguards were easily found in Tolea Biqua, and sometimes easily disposed of, as explained by the six-person security crew of a transport to [[Depatar/Legends|Depatar]]&mdash;they were marooned in Depatar, where they resorted to thuggery.<ref name="cp" />

The [[Cantina/Legends|bars]] in Tolea Biqua outnumbered all other business establishments combined. There was the usual range of bars from dives to upper establishments, but unlike many cities, their locations were not geographically delineated. Usually the names of the cantinas were also not helpful in determining which category it fell into. It was said that a new visitor would visit five bars and get in three fights before finding the right place to drink.<ref name="LFC" /> However, other dining establishments in the system (such as the [[Hutt's Tail]] in [[Nirama's public asteroid]]) were considered even worse than the worst bars in Tolea Biqua.<ref name="TW">{{LivingForce|Between the Worlds: TopWorld}}</ref>

Tolea Biqua was central to a yearly holiday called [[Festival]]. It began when the workers of [[Edic Bar]] were unexpectedly given the day off because they had finished production for the first operative [[G-59 Cannibalizer]] unit. They migrated to Tolea Biqua and its frequent drinking establishments to have a good time. The party ended up lasting four days, spreading through all the cities in Genarius and some cities in other planets of the Cularin system. Every year since then, on the anniversary of that party, Festival is celebrated.<ref name="LFC" /> This Festival was known to attract a wide variety of sentients, including most of the [[Pirate/Legends|pirate]] gang known as the [[Red Fury Brotherhood/Legends|Red Fury Brotherhood]], whose leader used the Festival as a reward for his men.<ref name="itsc">{{LivingForce|Clouds of Genarius: Into the Storm Clouds}}</ref>

The young thug gangs known as the [[Blood Velkers]]<ref name="LFC" /> and the [[Blood Raptors]]<ref name="POB" /> commonly caused trouble in this city. An occasional visitor of the city was playboy [[Xav Verivax]], who mixed with the local cream of the society.<ref name="LFC" />

In [[31 BBY/Legends|31 BBY]], [[Rodian/Legends|Rodian]] merchant [[Teeloo]] accidentally collided with a ship of the Blood Raptors while arriving to Genarius. Seven Raptors, under the lead of [[Scar Blenner]], ambushed him in his docking bay at Tolea Biqua, requised his cargo and challenged him to a mandatory race through [[Eskaron]] and back to Tolea Biqua, betting the cargo against his ship, the ''[[Neeva-Beelo]]''&mdash;an agreement they did not intended to honor. In fact, the Raptors attacked Teeloo's docking bay that same night, attempting to disable the ship. Teeloo managed to get the selfless aid of some good Samaritans and survived the race. Nevertheless, the race caused some losses to local crime lord [[Nirama]], who sent his lieutenant [[Len Markus]] and some minions to kidnap Teeloo, his friends and the Raptors, taking them to [[Mikish]].<ref name="POB" />

Later that same year, during the local Festival, most of the Brotherhood pirates were in Tolea Biquea, leaving their base partially unprotected. This was an essential part of [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Alec (Jedi)|Alec's]] plan to destroy [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] [[Karae Nalvas]]'s [[Conkesta|flying fortress]] near the core of Genarius. Alec's allies succeeded in this mission and left the doomed locale in a stolen ship. They crash-landed near some surprised [[SoroSuub Corporation/Legends|SoroSuub]] [[Sullustan/Legends|Sullustan]] executives who recognized their vehicle as a stolen prototype and rewarded them for that. Alec organized an honor reception for his friends during the Festival.<ref name="itsc" />

That year's celebration was particularly hectic: Tolea Biqua was shaken when a radiation storm damaged the generators and threaten to throw the whole city to the planetary core. This was avoided by several party attendants who risked their lives to stop the disaster.<ref name="BAb">''[[Blown Away]]'' (as described in [https://web.archive.org/web/20021221113407/www.wizards.com/rpga/livingforce/article.asp?x=lf/swlf20010913b_interactive&c=swlfc RPGA Living Force Interactive] on the [[Wikipedia:Internet_Archive#Wayback_Machine|Wayback Machine]])</ref> The party also saw a heated debate among representatives of the [[Metatheran Cartel]] and the SoroSuub Corporation, a recruitment attempt by the [[Thaereian military]], and the gift of an [[RK-720 Light Freighter]] to one of the attendants.<ref name="BWa">''[[Blown Away]]'' (as described in [https://web.archive.org/web/20021218152817/www.wizards.com/rpga/livingforce/article.asp?x=lf/swlf20010927b_transmissions&c=swlfc Transmissions From the Living Force Campaign] on the [[Wikipedia:Internet Archive#Wayback machine|Way back machine]])</ref>

